An international study led by Johns Hopkins University suggests that the rate of HIV - related dementia is high in sub - Saharan Africa that HIV dementia along with Alzheimer's disease and dementia from strokes may be among the common forms of dementia in the world.
A study carried out by British researchers has revealed that a drug designed to combat genital herpes can reduce levels of HIV in the blood by 70 percent and appears to reduce levels of HIV in the genital tract.
